# Simple PR Reviewer (Heuristic) · v0.1

A tiny, deterministic reviewer that analyzes PR diffs and posts inline annotations via GitHub Actions logging commands.
Useful as a baseline or to compare against any LLM reviewer (e.g., CodeRabbit).

## What it checks
- Large functions (line count threshold)
- Suspicious debug prints (`console.log`, `print`, `puts`, `dbg!`)
- `TODO`/`FIXME` left in code
- Potential secrets in added lines (basic regexes)
- New files without tests when `src/` changed
- Dangerous patterns: `eval`, `new Function`, `child_process.exec`, `exec(` in Python, SQL `SELECT *`
- Missing `types` in TS (very basic: `any` added)

## How it works
Workflow computes a diff for the PR (`base.sha..head.sha`) and pipes it to `tools/reviewer.js`.
The script emits `::warning file=...,line=...,title=...::message` so GitHub renders them as annotations on the "Checks" tab.

## Local run
```bash
git diff --unified=0 origin/main...HEAD | node tools/reviewer.js --stdin
